  "prompt": "What are the postings under SSC?",
  "response": "SSC stands for Staff Selection Commission, a government organization in India that conducts recruitment exams for various government departments and ministries. Some of the main postings under SSC include:\n\n1. Combined Graduate Level (CGL) exam postings:\n- Income Tax Inspector\n- Assistant in various government departments\n- Statistical Investigator\n- Junior Accountant\n- Compiler\n- Auditor\n\n2. Multi-Tasking Staff (MTS) exam postings:\n- Peon\n- Sweeper\n- Daftary\n- Chowkidar\n- Other support staff positions\n\n3. Combined Higher Secondary Level (CHSL) exam postings:\n- Lower Division Clerk (LDC)\n- Data Entry Operator\n- Postal Assistant\n- Sorting Assistant\n\n4. Constable (GD) in Central Armed Police Forces (CAPF)\n\n5. Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police and CAPFs\n\n6. Junior Engineer (Civil, Mechanical, Electrical, Quantity Surveying & Contract)\n\nThese postings cover various government departments and ministries, offering opportunities in administrative, technical, and support roles across different sectors.",
